# ---------- generated harness output ----------
# New-SmugglingPayload writes these; New-TamperedFixtures / Test-GitMotwPropagation
# produce similar trees. Never commit generated HTML bundles — each one has a
# fresh AES key inline and is large.
smuggle.html
expected.json
tampered.manifest.json

# common output-dir names used in the usage examples
/motw-test/
/motw-tamper/
/git-test/
/drop/
/fixtures-out/

# temp extraction / mount / clone workdirs (also emitted under $TEMP, but
# if a user passes a -WorkDir inside the repo tree, these patterns keep
# checkouts clean)
extract_*/
motwprop_*/
pwzip_*/
iso_*/
gitfix_*/
gitclone_*/
gite2e*/
innerwork_*/

# ---------- Pester / test output ----------
TestResults.xml
coverage.xml
*.trx

# ---------- Zone.Identifier sidecar files on non-Windows ----------
# On Linux/macOS the tampering generator (and some test fixtures) writes
# literal "<file>:Zone.Identifier" sidecars.  They're test artefacts, not
# source.  On Windows these filenames can't exist — the real ADS lives
# invisibly on the parent file — so this pattern is a no-op there.
*:Zone.Identifier

# ---------- OS / editor ----------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ---------- PowerShell / .NET ----------
*.ps1xml.bak
PSScriptAnalyzer.log
